   <b>OBJECTIVE</b>

   </br>A Senior Java Developer will participate in the specification of the overall design for implementing client software solutions.  You will be able to visualize the Java solution to realize the client’s requirements, working with the team to evaluate candidate technologies and approaches, and guiding software development to implement the solution.  As a senior Java developer, Nevo will expect you to possess the following characteristics:

   <ul class="listText">
   		<li>Constantly trying to increase your knowledge about Java technologies, and programming concepts in order to advance and improve your problem solving capabilities.
   		</li><li>Enjoy working smarter and not thinking through the details of each step in a project before proceeding forward.
   		</li><li>Able to work independently, while at the same time collaborating with others in order to make sure that the output of your work meets the client’s requirements.
   		</li><li>Committed to creating high business value software using iterative, collaborative, quality driven approaches.
   		</li><li>Efficient at solving programming problems with an emphasis on a practical perspective and consider the design, implementation, and testability and impact on the overall system life cycle.
   		</li><li>Disciplined to maintain high quality, tested code that realizes the requirements of the business application.
   		</li><li>Driven to working hard to complete projects at a pace that allows you to maintain the intensity and quality of your work.
   		</li>
   </ul>

   <b>ESSENTIAL QUALIFICATIONS</b>

   <ul class="listText">
		<li>5+ years of Java / J2EE experience
		</li><li>3+ years experience with end-to-end design of Object-Oriented J2EE applications J2EE (EJB, Java Servlet, JSP, JDBC, JNDI, JMS and XML)
		</li><li>Experience with HTML, EJB, JavaScript, Struts, SOAP, WCM, Apache, Tomcat
		</li><li>Experience with RDBMS databases (SQL Server, Oracle)
		</li><li>BS or BA in a computer science or equivalent technical experience
		</li><li>Demonstrated accomplishments designing and implementing complex software systems
		</li><li>Experience with UML, Use Case Analysis, prototyping, iterative development and related tools
		</li><li>Strong understanding of software development methodologies, especially agile software development approaches
		</li><li>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills with an appreciation for and ability to communicate with and respond to the needs of diverse audiences
		</li><li>Excellent writing skills; the ability to write clear, concise, comprehensive documents tailored to both technical and business audiences
		</li><li>Comfortable in a multi-task, deadline-oriented environment
		</li>
   </ul>

   <b>ADDITIONAL CONSIDERATIONS</b>

   <ul class="listText">
   		<li>Our clients include large corporations as well as higher education institutions whose requirements are diverse and constantly changing.
   		</li><li>Our projects often include the entire Software Development Life Cycle, and all layers of system architecture and design - from database design, through the business layer design and implementation, to both web-based and rich client implementations.
   		</li><li>Nevo will consider only direct applications by principals
   		</li><li>No relocation benefits are available for this position
   		</li><li>All applicants must be able to demonstrate authorization to work in the United States by their start date.
		</li>
   </ul>

